transcript.text: Hello, welcome back to the On Print Shop Store Management tutorial series.
In this video we will learn about how to store auto profiling.
The auto profiling feature allows your corporate or private store customers to use their information in PDF block templates by entering form fields.
This form field will be available to all the store customers in their My Account section.
The data that customers will enter in this form will be used for PDF block personalization when we enable it while creating a PDF block template.
So let's walk you through the steps to allow your customers auto profiling.
First, go to the admin panel, navigate to the Templates section and then click on the PDF block templates.
Here you need to select a PDF block template for which you want to enable the auto personalization.
You can also create a PDF block template following the steps we have shared in another video for how to create PDF block templates.
Now, after selecting the template, click on the actions drop down and then select Edit Info.
On the edit screen, Scroll down the page and locate the centralized personalization.
Enable this setting and then click on Save and back.
The next step is creating the store fields.
For this go to the Store management section and click on the stores.
Select the store for which you are creating these fields.
Click on the actions drop down and then select store fields.
To create new store fields click on the Add button.
Here you have to first select the type.
For this it will be User Wise personalization or Template personalization.

With user wise personalization, the end user as well as the admin will be able to enter the details in the fields whereas the template personalization can only be managed by the admin and it will be available as a drop down for PDF block templates.
Next, give a title for the field that will appear on the front end.
Let's create a store field for the username.
If you want to enter any description then you do so in the space provided.
Now you have to link the block name with the store field.
As we are creating a field for the block, let's link this with the name block.
Now define the user type.
Select if you want to display this field under any group, give a sorting order and enable the status of the field.
The next setting is to define how you will get the data for this field from your customers.
As we are creating a name field, let's keep this as text box type.
Select options for validation if it is required for any field.
We are keeping this as Allow null as the name will not need any validation.
If you want to add any default value, you can add it here.
Once done with all the configuration, click on save and back and you have created a store field linked with a block.
Similarly you can create other store fields.
Now on the front store, the customers can find the store fields in the My Account menu.
From the header link.
Click on the My Account menu and then click on the store fields.
You can see that we have created some store fields for the customers to fill up their details.
After adding all the details, click on Submit.
Now for auto profiling, go to the Product section and select a template for personalization.
From the Browse Design page in the Designer Studio, you can verify that the blocks are displaying the data from the store fields.
This is how you can configure and allow your customers to do auto profiling in the PDF block templates.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.

Every element form is associated with the specific block of templates, and at studio page, filled data will be auto populated on associated block data.
